{"serial": "24003", "department_serial": 68, "code": "LS1006", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "News and perspectives in Life Science", "ch": "生命科學時事導讀"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Huang, Chia-Yu", "Yeh, Shu-Dan"], "ch": ["黃佳瑜", "葉淑丹"]}, "credits": 1, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 1, "session": ["6"]}, "loc": {"building": "S5", "room": "112"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "生命科學系", "en": "Department of Life Sciences"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 42, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "The course aims to enhance students‘ connection to and understanding of biological events in everyday life by reading biology-related news or short articles and engaging in class discussions. Through this approach, students will develop their ability to critically analyze contemporary life science topics and improve their oral communication skills. By linking biological concepts to real-world events, the course will inspire greater interest in the impact of life sciences on society and encourage thoughtful engagement with current biological issues.\nBy the end of the course, students will be able to:\n•Demonstrate critical thinking skills by identifying and evaluating the scientific validity and relevance of the biological content presented in various news and articles.\n•Apply biological concepts and principles to explain real-world phenomena and contemporary life science issues covered in the media.\n•Communicate their insights and analyses effectively in both group discussions and oral presentations.\n•Engage thoughtfully in class discussions, providing evidence-based opinions and arguments on complex biological issues, demonstrating improved scientific literacy and oral communication.", "en": "The course aims to enhance students‘ connection to and understanding of biological events in everyday life by reading biology-related news or short articles and engaging in class discussions. Through this approach, students will develop their ability to critically analyze contemporary life science topics and improve their oral communication skills. By linking biological concepts to real-world events, the course will inspire greater interest in the impact of life sciences on society and encourage thoughtful engagement with current biological issues.\nBy the end of the course, students will be able to:\n•Demonstrate critical thinking skills by identifying and evaluating the scientific validity and relevance of the biological content presented in various news and articles.\n•Apply biological concepts and principles to explain real-world phenomena and contemporary life science issues covered in the media.\n•Communicate their insights and analyses effectively in both group discussions and oral presentations.\n•Engage thoughtfully in class discussions, providing evidence-based opinions and arguments on complex biological issues, demonstrating improved scientific literacy and oral communication."}, "outline": {"ch": "週次week課程內容Course topic\n1Course introduction\n2AI n protein structure\n3AI in diseases\n4Using DNA to store data\n5Animals with virgin births\n6Apple varieties\n7Chimpanzees self-medicate with plants\n8Species Evolution-Darwin‘s finches\n9Oral presentation\n10Explosive Pollen Wars: Plants Compete for Pollinator Space\n11Protein interactions: party is on\n123D-printed using human cells\n13The genome sequencing of yellow jacket\n14Selfish DNA: early development\n15Gut Health\n16Oral presentation\n17Student Self-directed Learning\n18Student Self-directed Learning", "en": "週次week課程內容Course topic\n1Course introduction\n2AI n protein structure\n3AI in diseases\n4Using DNA to store data\n5Animals with virgin births\n6Apple varieties\n7Chimpanzees self-medicate with plants\n8Species Evolution-Darwin‘s finches\n9Oral presentation\